Methods in it.uniroma3.mat.extendedset that return types with arguments of type IndexedSet
 java.util.List<? extends IndexedSet<T>> IndexedSet.powerSet()
          Computes the power-set of the current set.

It is a particular implementation of the algorithm Apriori. The power-set does not contains the empty set. The list is sorted according to the lexicographical order provided by the sorted set.
 java.util.List<? extends IndexedSet<T>> IndexedSet.powerSet(int min, int max)
          Computes a subset of the power-set of the current set, composed by those subsets that have cardinality between min and max.

It is a particular implementation of the algorithm Apriori. The power-set does not contains the empty set. The list is sorted according to the lexicographical order provided by the sorted set.
